text: "Minorities are criminals ... and that's a Fox story".  --- It would be so nice if Hollywood could make movies and TV shows without injecting political viewpoints.  It would be nice if they could just stick to the story without having to bash Fox News just because they are not a left leaning propaganda channel.  It's such a shame because pissing off half the country just reduces the appeal of their movies.  They just can't help themselves.  Many Republicans and Independents would probably like to see this movie but they know that the facts will be distorted be the far left leaning script writers who keep on bending the truths with more lies.  Never has anyone on Fox News said that "minorities are criminals".  Someone may have said that among the unvetted immigrants entering the country there may be some criminals among them.  That is NOT the same thing!  Words have consequences and the scriptwriters have most likely never even watched Fox News.  It's the evolution of gossip in the media that takes words out of context and interprets them with a completely different meaning, in the end.  I've watched the lying pundits on both sides and I'm not saying the right doesn't lie about what the left has to say but the right never injects political viewpoints in their movies. NEVER.  I've never seen a movie where the rich and successful guy is the good guy and the poor one is the bad guy.  In fact, "Slumdog millionaire","Titanic" and countless others won the Oscar!  The rich are always "evil"...  The last movie was "The Joker" and I predict it will win an Oscar.  I would have loved to see this movie but the script already showed me the bias and B.S. in the first 20 seconds of the trailer. Even the trailer starts with politically motivated lies!  Such a shame...
